The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Tuesday, August 05, 2003 				 Double blot 
																								Islamabad, Aug. 4 (PTI): Pakistan President Pervez Musharraf today said religious extremism and fundamentalism are responsible for tarnishing the image of the country and said the government was taking every measure to eradicate them.																								There is a need to correct them by following rational and pragmatic policies that project the country as a modern, tolerant and enlightened Islamic nation, he said.
